10-21-80 3

As a matter of fact it is quite possible that my failure to understand, for six and a half years, that both continua were equally real may be due to an unconscious A or not-A either-or Aristotelian mode of thinking on my part; I saw USA 1974 and I saw Rome AD 4S and my ossified brain components said, "One must be real and the other not real," but another part of my brain, less rigid, less in the grip of conventional modes of logic, realized, "Both are real. Both equally exist. Further, both are one. They are modes, aspects or accidents --whatever you want to call it-- of a single essence. This is the only way you can explain syntonic superimposition. Now, if the superimposition had been competitive --that would have required another theory entirely. I guess in that case I could have inferred something about time and space not being real, but I could not infer that the spatiotemporal continua were aspects of a common substratum a common essence. There would simply have confronted me a breakdown of the ordering categories of space and time, with no inference to be drawn by a tautalogy: space and time as ordering categories broke down and I saw two spaces and two times superimposed ... what we normally mean by a double exposure. But, see, one harmonious reality was formed by the two; so the great inference of accidents --two sets of accidents-- to a common essence took place in my brain, whereupon the realization came to my brain that space and time were not the best or the only way of ordering reality but that it could better be ordered morphologically. And then I found in TEARS where the USA, the USSR, Nazi Germany and ancient Rome and melded into one society -- oh yes; to that add futuristic elements. So we have five societies, five space-time continua as a single matrix. The strangest most eerie thought just struck me. If USA 1974 and Rome AD 45 are two spatiotemporal aspects of a common essence they as aspects if superimposed would clash, not blend -- this despite the common essence; I don't know why I know this but I do. But if it's really Rome AD 45 then they would blend, because the percipient would see that USA 1974 is Rome AD 45. What I have been calling a superimposition is more like a metamorphosis. A certain building is a building in Syria in the first century AD. Reality is seen under the aspect of Rome AD 45, the Holy Land. As if reverting. I noticed palm trees and sand, the warm wind, the relaxing people ... like a scene in ancient Syria. This is like the form-reversion in UBIK.


